When Cursor auto-generates a Git commit message for this repository (Source Control sparkle button or commit message AI), ALWAYS use Conventional Commits:

<type>(<scope>): <subject>

- type: feat | fix | docs | refactor | chore | build | ci | test | perf | revert
- scope (required): api | web | contracts | deps | ci | docs | root
- subject: imperative English, no trailing period, max 100 chars on first line

Examples:
- feat(api): migrate posts and comments oRPC handlers
- fix(api): remove duplicate /api prefix in oRPC handler
- chore(deps): add commitlint for conventional commits

Never use plain "Add ..." without type and scope. Never add Co-authored-by or AI attribution trailers.
